comment_data.body:
@llllvvuu I'll be happy to share more info once I better nail down the problematic code :)

> I wonder if my issue may be related: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/25157

Sounds related indeed. FWIW I've also been working with Lua when experiencing these crashes.

@llllvvuu oh you got a repro? Nice :D (well not nice but at least I know it's not just me lol).

> By the way, how do you get MacOS to pop up a crash report? When my Neovim crashes, it just does so silently

After Neovim quits, I run `open -a Console` from the terminal and open the "Crash Reports" tab.

I've tried doing some pretty esoteric edits on large Lua files, but I can't reproduce this anymore. Maybe I need to have some plugins installed that create big and/or weird extmarks?

You could also try instrumenting your build with something like this (or have a permanent nvim server running under lldb, but that's more invasive):

```diff
diff --git a/src/nvim/marktree.c b/src/nvim/marktree.c
index 627efa9e9..b3ac421d7 100644
--- a/src/nvim/marktree.c
+++ b/src/nvim/marktree.c
@@ -52,6 +52,7 @@
 
 #include "klib/kvec.h"
 #include "nvim/garray.h"
+#include "nvim/log.h"
 #include "nvim/marktree.h"
 #include "nvim/memory.h"
 #include "nvim/pos.h"
@@ -354,6 +355,18 @@ static void unintersect_node(MarkTree *b, MTNode *x, uint64_t id, bool strict)
     }
   }
   if (strict) {
+    if (!seen) {
+      ELOG("%s %" PRId16 " %" PRId16 " %" PRId32 " %" PRIu64 " %" PRIu64 " %" PRIu64 " %" PRIu64,
+        mt_inspect(b, true, true).data,
+        x->p_idx,
+        x->level,
+        x->n,
+        id,
+        kv_A(x->intersect, i),
+        mt_dbg_id(id),
+        mt_dbg_id(kv_A(x->intersect, i))
+      );
+    }
     assert(seen);
   }
``` 

It would show what the broken state is, but not how we get to the broken state (for that, would need to either have a recording or figure out the trigger)
